OL,3,CChancellor denies delaying infected
OL,4,Cblood compensation payouts
OL,6,FTo date, more than 3,000 people who
OL,7,Fcontracted illnesses through infected
OL,8,Fblood have died.
OL,10,FA public inquiry was set up in 2017 -
OL,11,Fhearing evidence from hundreds of
OL,12,Fpeople affected - before its final
OL,13,Frecommendations to compensate them
OL,14,Fwere made last year.
OL,16,FSome 82 people have died since the
OL,17,Finquiry recommended full compensation
OL,18,Fto those affected in April 2023.
